## Building the Snake Game in Vue 3

**Mental model:** The snake is an array of `{x,y}`; the head is index 0. Each tick prepend a new head and pop the tail — unless food was eaten (grow). Direction is a plain variable (not reactive) read inside the tick so it's never stale, and 180° reversals are rejected.

### Step 1 — State + direction
```js
const snake = ref([{ x: 7, y: 7 }]);
const food = ref({ x: 3, y: 3 });
let dir = { x: 1, y: 0 };
```

### Step 2 — Tick
```js
function tick() {
  const head = { x: snake.value[0].x + dir.x, y: snake.value[0].y + dir.y };
  if (hitsWall(head) || hitsSelf(head)) { over.value = true; return; }
  const grew = head.x === food.value.x && head.y === food.value.y;
  const next = [head, ...snake.value];
  if (grew) { food.value = randomFreeCell(next); } else { next.pop(); }
  snake.value = next;
}
```

### Step 3 — Keyboard with reversal guard
```js
function setDir(d) { if (d.x !== -dir.x || d.y !== -dir.y) dir = d; }
```

### Step 4 — Interval + cleanup
```js
onMounted(() => { id = setInterval(tick, 150); window.addEventListener('keydown', onKey); });
onUnmounted(() => { clearInterval(id); window.removeEventListener('keydown', onKey); });
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| 180° reversal | Reject opposite direction. |
| Food on snake | Re-roll until free. |
| Cleanup | Clear interval + key listener on unmount. |

**Interview tip:** Keeping `dir` as a plain (non-reactive) variable read inside `tick` is deliberate — it avoids both stale-closure issues and needless reactivity for a value that doesn't drive rendering.

